    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Ambassador in the Soviet Union (
                        Harriman
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945v05</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d824</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">824</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-08-08T12:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-08-08T12:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-08T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-08T12:00:00-05:00" n="824" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d824">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94114 Supplies/8–845: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-08T20:00:00+03:00">August 8, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 8—6 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2807. ReDeptel 1740, August 4. Text of proposal to Japanese re shipment by air of
                    relief supplies to internees sent to Foreign Office today. No mention made of
                    possibility of later asking Soviets for use of Soviet pilots as I believe no
                    practical benefit would accrue by taking up this subject now.<note n="53" xml:id="d824fn53">Marginal notation: “Academic now.”</note> We will do so
                    later in case Japanese turn down our proposal.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
